USAGE & RIGHTS NOTICE
=====================

This repository is a personal, non-commercial research database about the novelist
Donna Tartt. It mixes two very different kinds of material, with different terms.

1. ORIGINAL RESEARCH & COMPILATION (mine)
-----------------------------------------
The original text, analysis, organization, manifests, indexes, transcriptions, and
documentation authored for this project — e.g. `Donna_Tartt_Collectors_Reference.md`,
`About_Donna_Tartt_Items.md`, `README.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, the files in
`reports/`, `reference/`, `data/`, `wikipedia/`, `scripts/`, and the interview
transcriptions and book excerpts — are released under:

    Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International (CC BY-NC 4.0)
    https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/

You may share and adapt this original work for non-commercial purposes with attribution.

2. THIRD-PARTY SOURCE MATERIAL (not mine)
-----------------------------------------
Much of `assets/` consists of third-party material captured as research evidence:
cover images, scanned pages and full books, magazine and newspaper articles, dealer and
auction listings, and saved web pages. Copyright in those works remains with their
respective owners. They are reproduced here in good faith, in limited form, for
non-commercial study, commentary, and reference only. No claim of ownership is made over
any third-party work, and inclusion here does not grant you any rights to it.

If you own rights to something in this repository and would like it removed or corrected,
please open an issue or contact the repository owner, and it will be taken down promptly.

This notice is provided in plain language and is not legal advice.
